               <scopecontent id="aspace_eff1fc5b6b92a4fb15752e901593367d">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Schrieb-kalender used for this diary is from a different printer than the Schrieb-Kalenders used for all other diaries in the collection; a page is provided for every month instead of for every week.</p>
                  <p>Diary does not contain entries from April through December (pages are present, but blank).</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="aspace_410daa424bf36b7bb79f882c85d832e6" level="item">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Diary</unittitle>
                  <unitdatestructured unitdatetype="inclusive">
                     <datesingle standarddate="1805">1805</datesingle>
                  </unitdatestructured>
                  <container altrender="Paige 15"
                             id="aspace_35dae3e283435cbda1be1680b02dfd4b"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="Box">1</container>
               </did>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_8fc4fecf8b1345e45d1c8550d9518426">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>This volume is encrypted with a cipher created by Joseph von Chlingensberg auf Berg.</p>
                  <p>Laid in at front of volume are notes on cipher translation from multiple sources: a contemporary source (likely Joseph von Chlingensberg Auf Berg's son, also named Joseph von Chlingensburg), a 20th century owner, and possibly Jonathan Hill.</p>
                  <p>A number of pages appear to have been cut out from the volume entirely; the first printed date that appears is the week of August 18th. Parts of other pages also appear to have been cut out.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
